Acceptance Criteria:

 • showQuote remains the only control for Estimator ↔ Quote inside the estimator feature shell.
 • No Phase 1 implementation introduces route-driven quote state.
 • /portal is guarded; /estimator remains stable and independently testable.
 • Portal UI uses approved lifecycle enums only.
 • Case-study email sends exclusively through Supabase Edge Function under /make-server-07a007e1.
 • No lucide-react is introduced.

Risks and assumptions

 • The main repo guideline says not to implement react-router-dom inside the estimator app itself, so the router must live at the shell boundary, not inside estimator feature internals.
 • If you later want deep-linkable quote detail pages, that should be a Phase 2 project after the shell migration is stable.
 • Portal data should start with typed mocks and mapper functions before any database normalization work.

